headline.main: MOSCOW-SOFIA TIE FEARED NEAR END; Soviet Flatly Rejects Bulgar Protest on Alleged Activity of Red Army Parachutists

lead_paragraph: ANKARA, Turkey, Sept. 23 -- Moscow's flat rejection of Sofia's new protest against alleged operations of Red Army parachutists in the Bulgarian Dobruja is viewed in leading foreign diplomatic and military circles at Ankara tonight as the penultimate or perhaps even final step before a rupture of the diplomatic relations between the Soviet Union and Bulgaria.
